PROPERTY NEWS - The correct maintenance of gate motors is crucial for safety, reliability and long-term performance.


> Follow these safety guidelines when maintaining your gate motor:


- Switch off the power supply before cleaning, inspecting or repairing any motor components;
- Clear the gate path of stones, overgrowth and any obstacles that could block the motor’s movement;
- Inspect the gate arms and wheels for damage and check for rust on the chain;
- Lubricate moving parts such as gears and chains with the correct gate lubricant to ensure smooth operation.
- Regularly test all the safety features to ensure they work correctly;
- Store remotes and keypads in a safe place;
- Familiarise yourself with the manual release mechanism in case of power outages;
- Ensure the gate cannot be easily lifted off its rails;
- Monitor the battery’s health, particularly during frequent load-shedding, as it might require replacement earlier than the usual two to three years.

By following these steps, you can extend the lifespan of your gate motor and reduce the risk of malfunction or accidents.

Article: Caxton publication, The Citizen

